CAPTAIN PARTY chased two to three wide down the backstretch before tipping four wide through the turn placed to coaxing at the three-eighths, continued four wide into upper stretch, kept on under a drive to the finish but was out-finished in the late stages. Z DANCER broke out at the start bumping ALL GOOD HERE against CHULLIGAN and causing half the pressure that pinched back that second rival, pressed the pace of BORN DANCER from the outside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths on near even terms, swung three wide into upper stretch, weakened in the late going. FERRIS MULER broke in at the start and bumped CHULLIGAN, then got bumped by CHULLIGAN and pinched that foe back in tandem with pressure inside from Z DANCER, chased briefly just off the inside and got steadied near the seven-eighths shuffling back GOSSIPING PANDO in behind, chased along the inside before darting out four wide inside the nine-sixteenths, went six wide through the far turn coaxed along from the three-eighths, continued six wide into upper stretch and made no late headway. CHULLIGAN got bumped at the start by FERRIS MULER and then bumped again by ALL GOOD HERE due to pressure from Z DANCER and was pinched back and steadied out between foes conceding five lengths to the front, came under urging and chased three to four paths off the inside down the backstretch, tipped five wide through the far turn coaxed along from the three-eighths, went seven wide into upper stretch, made no headway through to the finish. UNAFFECTED chased just off the inside down the backstretch and then four wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung four to five wide into upper stretch, offered no response. GOSSIPING PANDO away towards the rear, got shuffled back when FERRIS MULER steadied back directly in front, chased three then two wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and offered no response. BORDER PATROL chased three wide just off the top pair, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went four wide into upper stretch and tired. OYSTA chased along the inside, grew detached at the tail of the field nearing the far turn, spun just off the inside into upper stretch well behind and unable to make an impact, and was eased home to the finish.
